@startuml
title Smartcard logon via Kerberos PKINIT

actor User
participant "Client (LSASS)" as Client
participant "Smartcard / TPM" as Card
participant "KDC\n(Domain Controller)" as KDC

User -> Card : insert card, enter PIN
Client -> Card : request signature over\npre-auth data (timestamp)
Card -> Card : sign with non-exportable\nprivate key
Card --> Client : signed AS-REQ pre-auth
Client -> KDC : AS-REQ (PKINIT)\n+ user certificate
KDC -> KDC : validate cert chain\nagainst trusted PKI
KDC -> KDC : check revocation (CRL/OCSP)
KDC --> Client : AS-REP\n(TGT + session key,\nPAC_CREDENTIAL_INFO with NTLM)
Client -> KDC : TGS-REQ (with TGT)
KDC --> Client : service ticket
note over Client, KDC
  From here the flow is ordinary
  Kerberos: tickets behave the
  same as password-based logon.
end note
@enduml
